OL,3,CShoplifting offences in England and
OL,4,CWales hit a 20-year high
OL,6,FPromising to put more police on the
OL,7,Fstreets, Ms Cooper emphasised the need
OL,8,Ffor people "to feel safe on the
OL,9,Fstreets."
OL,11,FMeghan Elkin, from the ONS, said:
OL,12,F"There has been no change across many
OL,13,Fcrime types in the last year. However,
OL,14,Fwe have seen falls in fraud while
OL,15,Fthere have been increases in computer
OL,16,Fmisuse and some forms of theft, such
OL,17,Fas shoplifting and theft from the
OL,18,Fperson. Notably, shoplifting has
OL,19,Fcontinued to see increases and remains
OL,20,Fat its highest level in 20 years.
